Setup Before we can test a panic, we need to have code that panics.
package panic func willPanic() { panic(&quot;Told you I would panic&quot;) }  Testing Given that we know the code will panic, we can do the following:
package panic import ( &quot;testing&quot; ) func TestWillPanic(t *testing.T) { defer func() { if r := recover(); r == nil { t.Errorf(&quot;The code did not panic&quot;) } }() //Call func willPanic() }  In the above, we try to recover and, if the recovery is equal to nil, we marked the test as failed.

